  "title": "Universal Command and Control Language Early System Engineering: Performance Effects of a Universal Command and Control Standard",
  "abstract": "The U.S. Department of Defense (DoD) requires more efficient and timely methods to acquire, integrate, and interoperate systems and systems-<em>of</em>-systems (SoSs) to deter near-peer adversaries and prevail in combat. RAND researchers were asked to participate in a multiyear effort to help DoD understand the challenges of creating a universal command and control language to facilitate the evolution of systems and interoperability of SoSs.",
